import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['x'], data['y'])
    plt.xlabel('x-coordinate')
    plt.ylabel('y-coordinate')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between x and y coordinates?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['x'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='x coordinates')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Mean: {data["x"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('X Coordinates')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of x coordinates?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['y'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='y coordinates')
    plt.axvline(data['y'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['y'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('y coordinates')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of y coordinates?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = np.sqrt(data['x']**2 + data['y']**2)
    median_distance = data['distance'].median()
    
    plt.hist(data['distance'], bins=10, alpha=0.7, color='blue', label='Distances')
    plt.axvline(median_distance, color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Median Distance: {median_distance:.2f}')
    
    plt.xlabel('Distance from Origin')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the distance of points from the origin?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = np.sqrt(data['x']**2 + data['y']**2)
    avg_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    
    plt.scatter(data['x'], data['y'], label='Points')
    plt.axhline(avg_distance, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('X Coordinate')
    plt.ylabel('Y Coordinate')
    plt.title('What is the average distance of points from the origin?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
